<div><h3>ENG 1320 - Green Fire: Modern Fantasy </h3>  <hr>This course examines the rise and development of the fantasy novel in the 20th Century by looking into its beginnings in Britain, and its adoption and expansion by American authors. While the readings for the course are necessarily limited to major figures in both countries, mention will be made to other practitioners of the genre, such as Lewis and Rowling, as well as landmark associations between the authors such as the Inklings.<br><br><strong>Course Designation/Attribute:</strong> VE<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> 201905<br><br></div>		</td>
